<activity><title>Function Notation</title>

            <commentary audience="instructor"><title>Note</title>
            <p>When discussing function notation, emphasize that in the equation <m>y=f(x)</m>, <m>f</m> is not a variable, the parentheses in <m>f(x)</m> do not indicate a product, and <m>f(x)</m> is the output variable, or another name for <m>y</m>.</p></commentary>

